wdi-EG.GDP.PUSE.KO.PP.def: GDP per unit of energy use is the PPP GDP per kilogram of oil equivalent of energy use. PPP GDP is gross domestic product converted to current international dollars using purchasing power parity rates based on the 2017 ICP round. An international dollar has the same purchasing power over GDP as a U.S. dollar has in the United States.
wdi-EG.GDP.PUSE.KO.PP.name: GDP per unit of energy use
wdi-EG.GDP.PUSE.KO.PP.dim: PPP $ per kg of oil equivalent
wdi-EG.GDP.PUSE.KO.PP.units: PPP $ per kg of oil equivalent
